comment: First draft of a new, fast dependency JSR-330 injector.
Address code review comments from bob@ and edenman@
New, very basic Java code generator.
Centralize naming of fields and parameters.
New annotation-driven API that uses entry points.
Fix bugs that were breaking the injector's first client.
Minimal support for Guice annotations to ease migration and A/B testing.
Fix many injector bugs to run Square apps.
Use raw types for supertype bindings.
Use raw types for supertype bindings.
Stop requiring that all modules have at least one @Provides method.
Initial infrastructure to generate modules from AndroidManifest.xml.
Build time graph construction and validation.
Permit a module to declare child modules.
Prefer code gen over annotations for Module.children.
Add a main method to generate a module from an AndroidManifest.xml.
Add an option to exclude an activity or service as an entry point.
Add a Lazy<T> with a delegate binding, so consumers can @Inject a Lazy<T> if T is bound. Tighten up key mangling code
Retry making 'complete=true' the default for modules.
Add an example of injecting Lazy<T> into the CoffeeMaker app.
Don't spam the logs when a generated class is not found.
Add some documentation for Lazy<T> and fix Provider<T> docs to make them less preferred.
Update the Providers doc section to address review comments.
Make Provider<T> documentation even more terse.
Rename Module's property children to includes, and generally rename all internals to reflect this, leaving children in place but deprecated pending conversion of all callers.
Add support for multi-bindings, such that any method annotated with Provide AND Element contribute that binding to a set-binding, which builds an injectable set at injection time.
Be consistent about the project's location.
Use http for the namespace instead of https.
Use reflection names for annotation inner classes: '$' instead of '.'.
Add parent pom for deployment to central.
Add support for multi-bindings in code generation.
Abstract Android-specific manifest generation to simple static API.
Make the Android manifest module a proper maven plugin.
Do not generate an $InjectAdapter for classes with only static injections
Updating dagger-androidmanifest-plugin Maven packaging from jar to maven-plugin
Uppercase for the first letter of the generated module binding inner classes. See #46.
Make ObjectGraph.get() lazy and remove getLazy().
Use a bitfield for Binding.linked and Binding.singleton.
Use a real cycle detection algorithm in Dagger.
Print better errors when annotation types mismatch.
Revert "Print better errors when annotation types mismatch."
New failure messages when annotation types mismatch.
Don't require entry point classes to have @Inject annotations.

Clean up the travis config to do a proper deps install, execute a full phase build cycle (up to verify rather than merely test) and ensure that the invoker plugin (which will come later) doesn't execute during dependency installation.

Make dot-writer avoid getDependencies() on UNRESOLVED bindings, since not ever wiring fed to the dot-writer will be a valid graph spec.  Also, add a toString() on binding so it shows up in debugging, and ensure that a failed binding write (to a dot file) has a wrapped exception that is clearer.
Add invoker-based integration tests of the build (including code-generation) to allow for expected failing builds to be tested and verified.
Change all poms to two-space indentation to match code.
Make UNRESOLVED be effectively a null object, and use it polymorphically.
Migrate code-gen processors to their own project, and separate reflection code.
Make it more clear who is lazy
Fix a fix for a fix

Extension graphs.  Allow a graph to be extended such that extension graph instances will delegate up the chain if they can't satisfy dependencies.  This can be used to implement a 'scope' concept by creating a new extension graph with modules for those appropriately scoped objects being created and collected at the start and end of each scope.
Handle modules with no constructor when passed in as a class and add a test case to ensure that modules included by modules can be instantiated if they're not passed in as instances.
Documentation, style and small renaming changes.
Add goal prefix to Maven plugin for short invocation.
Generating unique ClassBinding name per method signature
Synchronizing calls to linker.requestBinding so linking happens in an atomic operation
Unbreak Graph.plus. We broke it when we added synchronization.
Don't require entry points to have injectable constructors.
Test for exercising an entry point that cannot be created.
Do not attempt to build gh-pages branch.
Correct commit message for website deploy.
Use relative paths to static directory.
Switch multi-value @Provides to use Type enum.
Change android manifest plugin default to ManifestModule.
Allow manifest module generator invocation as Ant task.
Need at least one public API for javadoc to run during release.
Fix code block in the readme file.
Never say 'null required by' in an error message.
Don't wrap runtime exceptions thrown by user code.
Fix a bug where we were requiring injectable supertypes in dagger-compiler.
Provide special casing for no-package types in the generation of adapters.  Also, add an integration test to prove this case works.
Enable and add more checkstyle rules.
Make compiler work with other code generators
Code review comments and refactored type persistance across passes in InjectorProcessor and ProvidesProcessor
Update website to refer to 'includes' rather than 'children'.
Fix dot-writer from breaking when there are missing bindings.  Display the erroneous binding as unbound instead.
Fix Inject processor to treat private and protected no-arg constructors like a missing no-arg constructor.
Fix all examples and the README doc to use an optional dep on the artifact instead of a plugin dep on the compiler, which doesn't produce the right results.
Loosen constraints so only private constructors are un-injectable.
Add test to detect missing provides methods from a bug in the processor, and fix the bug.
Add warnings to the maven build. Also add warnings display to the root project so we see our own warnings.

A re-work of the code-generation system to made generated code that is cleaner, more readble, more documented, with methods clustered together to line up infrastructure methods and methods that might reasonably be stepped-through in a debugger.  Along with this includes quite a few changes, including making generation of methods/fields conditional upon their being used, field names only being disambiguated when actually necessary, etc. Some other issues including bulk organization of imports an infrastructure for emitting javadocs, adding some integration tests to verify some things changed here, etc.
Add a SuppressWarnings annotation to suppress unchecked casts, plus a test.
Fix a crash in the dagger-compiler on parameterized injected types.
Fix regression by making Binding default behaviour to do nothing on getDependencies()
Switch default of injectMembers() to no-op and fix subclasses.
more conversions to AssertionError and move a comment into an exception message.
Pass location with errors in codegen to have markers in editors in Eclipse
Use getCanonicalName rather than getName when emitting source, by principle.
Remove redundant code re. finding no-args constructors.
Report error at codegen when child module is missing @Module annotation
Fix integration test: add missing invoker.properties
Upgrade to JavaWriter 1.0.2. Drop now-duplicated method.
Add cycle detection using the problem detector, plus test.
Return early on a graph validation failure, but continue to process other modules.
Make the verification test slightly saner.
Reject @Provides methods with 'throws' clause, at compile time.
Complaining about non-static inner class injection closes #68
Add RunWith annotations so Dagger can build from source inside customers' codebases and run in non-maven hosted test runners.
Move example into a sub-folder and create the structure to parent other examples.
Rework providesprocessor to generate ModuleAdapters even when no Provides methods are present.
Accept dagger.Module in the processor, and don't assert that this processor has completed all processing for dagger.Module.  Also fix some nits.
Demonstrate and fix problem with singletons when force-linked from a plus() operation.
Fix some exception text, add a better thrown error for inaccessible no-args constructors on modules, remove a redundant test, and rename a provides method.
add failing tests for validating that SingletonBinding delegates to the wrapped binding for getting/setting state. Signed-off-by: Andy Dennie <github@adennie.e4ward.com>
in linkRequested, call scope() to wrap singleton bindings (when appropriate) and then put the scoped binding onto both the toLink and bindings lists.
Renamed BindingTest to SingletonBindingTest and... -changed copyright year to 2013 -fixed ordering of imports to comply with Square style guide -added @RunWith -fixed isSingleton assertion
Capitalize comment and end with period.
Revert from throwing a friendlier error in a case that should never occur outside of an applet.
Make ObjectGraph itself an abstract type with five abstract contract methods (plus the static create()), moving the implementation into a static inner class.
Use SourceVersion.latestSupported() to avoid warning with JDK 7.
When flagging an override of an override, clarify that this is intentionally not support.
Fixed to use original message for non-override scenario.
Throw an error on a module inclusion cycle, and add a test.
Protect singleton and lazy bindings against concurrent access, and test that this works.
Move dagger-compiler as a m-compiler-p dependency.
Fix some style and naming issues from code-review.
Update README. Fix XML comment syntax.
Remove extra lock object per @swankjesse's concerns about object allocation on android.
Re-work a loop to better use the stack of path elements, and fix error messaging.
Test for erroneous message more explicitly.
Forbid modules who extend from non-Object class types.
Move back to optional dependency for the dagger-compiler.
Do not fail builds due to unforseen problems in GraphVizualizer.
Point download links at Maven Central.
Revert missed integration test to old dagger-compiler inclusion strategy.
Forbid Provider and Lazy as provides return type.
Unused @Provide methods cause compiler failures unless @Module(library=true)
Use maven-compiler-plugin 3.1 in compiler IT tests to fix platform-dependent issues
Migrate website to the new hotness.
Fix validation when passing an interface to the injects list.
Use two dollar signs between class name and dagger-generated suffix.
Fixing case where StaticInjections were incorrectly failing unused provider check Closes #216
Correct some problems with the Activity graph example.
Fix issues with problem detector when used at runtime.
Don't create objects unless there's an @Inject annotation.
Only hide internal javadocs from core.
Update deploy script to include javadocs.
It's not dagger-core. I am an idiot.
Ensure the correct groupId and artifactId are being used.
Fix a broken link on the dagger site.
Copy the note from the simple Android example into the scope example.
Add a RunsWith(JUnit4.clss) annotation to allow test to run inside google. ------------- Created by MOE: http://code.google.com/p/moe-java MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=46244288
Ensure the manifest points to the correct application.
Could not find tool 'aapt' error after updating android sdk
Helpful error message if someone puts @Inject on a class, rather than a NPE with no info
Handle the failure of compilation better, so we don't find out because of a ClassCastException on a TypeElement.
Rename the plugins to Loaders and re-work the packages a bit.
Include javax.inject in Readme when using jars.
Request classloading from the classloader of the requesting object, not Class.forName().
Re-name and slightly restructure much of the processor code, so that it is more obious what the pieces are. This is intended to improve future maintenance.
Add a check for Singleton on constructors.
add an integration test to prove the singleton on constructor check is failing builds as it should.
A configuration to permit travis to install the android SDK before running continuous build.
Reduce the set of things needed for building the android examples.
Rework the default loader into a cleaner, more explicit FallbackLoader, and turn the previously chained loaders into ingredients that could be used in this or other loaders.
Various fixes from review, including style fixes for square's codebase, typos, clean up some extra logging, etc.
Support all annotations, since some JVMs will only cause the module processor to run if that compilation job includes classes that have both @dagger.Provides and @dagger.Module.
Remove reflective fallback for modules (and provides methods), and clean up the attendant code.
Include DemoModule in module list for simple Android example.
Add some javadocs, plus more precisely narrow where an exception is caught.
Mark a fail-over case as such.
Fix (irrelevant) error in test, and strengthen it to ensure the right failure is being caught.
Fix an inverted conditional that was mistakenly inverted in the move to FailoverLoader and no reflection.
Add a proper test for FailoverLoader.
Rename TestOnlyModuleAdapter -> TestingModuleAdapter to line it up with TestingLoader.
Create a cache for class loading that both successfully loaded classes, as well as class lookup failures (using Void.class as a null object).
Make cache private - no access needed for testing.
Add a test for primitive injection in the code-gen, plus enough maven config to permit the annotations to run on the test sources (won't work in Eclipse, mind...)
Fix array handling so we don't attempt to box the primitive type the array is composed of.  It's not necessary, it's incorrect in the type-system, and it's not horrible to fix.
Some minor naming and spacing fixes.
Pass through prior errors so as to not hide real errors from the compilation job.
Provides methods should not be on classes unless they also are annotated as a Module.
Moved checkstyle to run before integration tests.
Added static checks for injected final fields, @Provides methods outside of modules, and validating the use of scoping and qualifier annotations.
Fix typo in AndroidModule.java in example
Update the change log for the new release date.
minor fixes: (1)removed extra blank line in generated adapters (2)changed binder-> binding in generated javadoc and method name
Add in Google's compile testing system, with an initial set of converted tests, and fix an escaped exception in GraphAnalysisProcessor uncovered in the process.
Add tests for @Module(library=true/false), as well as some initial code-gen tests.
Move integration tests into organized folders.
Split the scope-on-abstract tests a bit and rename.
Add lots of scope annotation validations to the test and delete invoker tests.
Rename test since it is all usages, both good and bad.
Move more scope tests into compile-testing style tests.
Re-order the tests, and add some links to compile-testing into TODOs.
Fix a test which was not broken, but had misleading text.  Also bump compile_testing and depend on guava explicitly, per maven recommendations.

Fix issue #322 by deferring the writing of the generated module adapter until all the generation is done in-memory, and interpret Error nodes from the AST more liberally, taking the raw type information from the text of the Error node.
Fix up set bindings to handle plus() graphs properly.
Remove now-unnecessary linker parent checking for lookup.
Narrow test's constraints, and add some spacing to DeferredBinding
Use String.concat in FailoverLoader for performance-critical concatenations of two Strings. ------------- Created by MOE: http://code.google.com/p/moe-java MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=54112486
Make ModuleAdapters stateless. ------------- Created by MOE: http://code.google.com/p/moe-java MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=54155756
Fix test to conform with stateless module adapters.
Revert a conversion from an array to a list (to avoid the extra unnecessary allocations) and deal with a few code review nits.
Use a ReadWriteLock rather than a single, global lock to memoize in dagger.
Prefer LHM over HashMap, and remove a stray synchronized keyword.
Add two failing tests and a change which causes them to pass for orphan analysis triggering on a provides binding that whose provided object is in the injects= list
Normalize builds by forcing deterministic behaviour in GraphVizualizer.  The same graph should result in the same .dot file.
Clean up (and improve performance of) the creation of member injection keys. ------------- Created by MOE: http://code.google.com/p/moe-java MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=54920552

Use Class.newInstance to instantiate Dagger classes.  Class.newInstance caches the constructor, so this should generally be a faster operation. ------------- Created by MOE: http://code.google.com/p/moe-java MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=54920411
Remove unused import constraint when applied to Javadoc, since that's eclipse's behaviour.
Propagate SetBindings settings in the copy constructor.
Make sure that set bindings respect the library setting on their contributing modules. ------------- Created by MOE: http://code.google.com/p/moe-java MOE_MIGRATED_REVID=54924803
Loosen the extent to which we trap and report exceptions.
backfill provides method test for the compiler
Fix Provides adapter generation when a provides method has a parameter named 'module'
Fix JIT binding attempts for generic or annotated keys.
Avoid duplicate work on .plus() by not re-linking all the bindings (or scanning them to determine if they need re-linking, etc.)
Revert "Remove now-unnecessary linker parent checking for lookup."
Propagate ONLY the SetBindings, not all bindings from the parent into the child, so memoization of linkAll() means anything.
Bump JavaWriter to track latest release.
A few more changes to eliminate reflection.
Update the Maven Android plugin for compatibility with Maven 3.1.
Add far JAR for users without a dependency manager.
Use the same tagline in the pom.
Revert "A few more changes to eliminate reflection."
Move tests to more appropriate locations.
Chain (instead of copy-construct) SetBindings.  Also, extract a BindingMap that treats SetBindings as first-class and sets them aside.
Fixes from pull request review in square/dagger#373.
Switch Queue to better performing Deque.
Switch Android example to use addsTo for a complete module.
Use a simpler means of installing the Android SDK.
Do not mask underlying exception message when binding.
fixed compile issue: Caused by: java.lang.ClassNotFoundException: com.android.sdklib.AndroidVersion$AndroidVersionException
Add an ArrayQueue (trimmed ArrayDeque from Android) and use it in Linker to restore Android API 8 (Java5) compatibility. Add animal-sniffer to ensure it.
Work around a bug in the Maven release plugin.
Deprecate G+ community in favor of StackOverflow.
Make the test for dependency cycles less brittle.
Fix up a case where we report errors poorly when state is wrong, usually becuase of inconsistency in what is passed in to ObjectGraph.create().
Make the test a little more explicit.
Use new central artifact redirect link.
Auto-deploy snapshots from Travis CI to Sonatype.
Switch Dagger 1.x from JavaWriter to JavaPoet.
Fix checkstyle by removing trailing spaces.
Update to the latest Maven Android plugin.
changing JavaWriter to JavaPoet in README.md file
allow use of dollar signs in processed class names
work-around bug in javac in Java 7
Remove synthetic accessor method generation by incresing visibility.
Upgrade test code to latest versions, standards.
Skip integration tests on snapshot deploy.
Remove generics for the superclass when generating inject adapters
Add a deprecation note to the website.
